Name: Vivecraft 1.16.2 v4 - Self-Appreciation
Body:
Revision 3 ( 9/15/2020)
 - Update forge to .61
 - Fix forge/multimc not loading if that version of forge had not been previously loaded standalone.
 - Fixed a crash when near someone fishing.
 - Fixed being able to right click on your mount in some cases.
 - Add German translations.

Initial Release (VR r2 8/31/2020)

 - Update Forge to .22. Fix some forge things.

 - Fix aspect ratio on undistorted mirror using shaders.

Initial Release (NONVR r1 8/31/2020)

 - Update Forge to .22. Fix some forge things.

Name: Vivecraft 1.16.1 v2 - Confusing What is Real
Body:
r2 (8/9/2020)
 - Fix init/render setup error messages not displaying.

r1 (8/7/2020)
 - Updated Optifine to G2 release and Forge to 32.0.106
 - **Roomscale Crawling** has been updated to have appropriate 3rd person animations (also affects swimming and flying). 
 - Added HUD icon for roomscale crawling.
 - The **Touch Hotbar** has been changed to use a context-sensitive click instead of just switching on touch.. 
 - The Touch Hotbar can also swap items by clicking on the 'offhand' slot.
 - Pigs and striders now move towards the on-a-stick item instead of just in the controller direction.
 - Made it a little harder to accidentally room-scale dismount a strider. Little buggers are fast.
 - Fixed not being able to connect to named servers using Java14
 - Fixed some projectiles not spawning correctly.
 - Fixed GUI not being visible when your face was in a block.
 - Fixed hitting 'cancel' in quick commands menu going to a blank screen.
 - Fixed a number of issues related to buckets.
 - Reworked system related to sending 'look' direction on vanilla servers. Ideally the player look direction follows the hmd in most cirumstances now on realms or other servers without a plugin. Let me know if we've broken something here.
 - Added Dutch translations. Click [here](https://www.transifex.com/techjar/vivecraft/) if you'd like to help translate Vivecraft.
 - If an item model has the CustomModelData tag, it will use the third_person_right_hand transform at a 70% scale, instead of the tweaked first person transforms that Vivecraft uses by default. If you want to fight about this come to discord.

r1 NonVR (8/7/2020)
 - Updated Optifine to G2 release and Forge to 32.0.106
 - Animation support for crawling/swimming/flying.

Name: Vivecraft 1.16.1 Beta - Nether Again
Body:
This is a pre-release. It includes a preview version of Optifine (pre10), and we expect 1.16.2 to launch very soon. For the very latest updates check our discord.

VR Client RC2 (8/4/2020)
 - Added **Roomscale Crawling**. Gettin' down on the floor will put you in the 'squished' pose so you can fit thought 1 block openings. You may need to turn this setting on in VR Settings > Interaction Settings. Requires VFE 1.2.0+ for Forge servers, and VSE r5+ for Spigot servers.
 - Fixed some angle issues with WMR controllers. Hopefully.
 - Bundled French translations, mais oui! Thanks, translators.
 - Added button in pause menu to move the 3rd person camera, if using.

VR Client RC1 (7/31/2020)
 - Added option to use ZGC on Java 14. (Highly recommend for performance!). 
 - Fix arrow speed in standing mode.
 - Fix view not shifting to match hitbox while swim-sprinting.
 - Fix game rendering freezing on linux. Other linux issues may still be present.

New in Vivecraft 1.16 Betas: (7/28/2020)
 - Forge is supported. We are also doing a optiforge-style re-processing of coremods so compatibility might actually be better than just optifine.
 - Vivecraft can now be localized. See [here](https://www.transifex.com/techjar/vivecraft/) if you'd like to help with translating Vivecraft. If your target language is not on the list, you can request for it to be added.
 - We recommend playing in *Fabulous!* graphics setting unless you're using shaders. Several of the hacks we were using to do decent alpha-sorting have been removed in lieu of doing it properly using vanilla's fabulous new render path.
